set up vagrant
==============

1) install vagrant for ubuntu

2) install virtualbox

3) create vagrant directory and run >> vagrant init debian/contrib-jessie

4) change Vagrantfile in directory to Ludos file

5) create src/ directory in vagrant directory

6) run >> vagrant plugin install vagrant-vbguest

7) >> vagrant up              should be set up correctly after some time

8) vagrant ssh to enter the machine

9) in machine: >> sudo apt-get install python-virtualenv python-pip git

10) git clone

11) >> virtualenv myEnv

12) enter virtualenv: >> source myEnv/bin/activate

13) >> pip install -r requirements.txt

